Aviation Safety Council of Taiwan ( ASC ) Repeatedly Delayed Investigation Report on Singapore Airlines Crash , Causing Prosecutors to Smell a Rat
( Taipei ) A year and half have passed since the plane crash of the Singapore Airlines , yet Aviation Safety Council of Taiwan ( ASC ) has delayed the investigation report on the plane crash again and again , stalling the investigation by Taoyuan district prosecutor's office and causing the prosecutors to smell a rat . As for ASC , it has promised to deliver the investigation report in April .
At 11 : 18 p . m . on October 31 , 2000 , the Singapore Airlines Flight SQ-006 at Chiang Kai-shek Airport bound for Los Angeles entered by error the runway # 05 on the right side during take-off and crashed into the two digging machines and exploded , killing 83 passengers and injuring nearly a hundred passengers .
China Times reported yesterday that Taoyuan district prosecutor's office in charge of prosecuting for criminal liability after the plane crash has had several disputes over the right to investigate with ASC investigation unit .
Since the plane crash , Wang Tiensheng , former chief prosecutor of Taoyuan prosecutor's office , has been promoted to chief prosecutor of Taichong . Chen Shouhuang serves as his replacement . The case prosecutor Huang Moushin has also been transferred to Taipei prosecutor's office , handing over the case to Chiang Yuanchen .
Meanwhile , the original due date of the investigation report at the end of last year promised by ASC was postponed to the end of January . After the end of January , it was again changed to February . So far there has been no news . Urged by the prosecutors , ASC now promises to deliver the report in April .
As Los Angeles was the destination of Flight SQ-006 , some of the victims' families have already taken the case to the US court for huge sums of civil compensation , suing not only Singapore Airlines but also Taiwan Civil Aviation Administration .
The lawsuit by the victims' families for compensation is tantamount to accusing Taiwan Aviation Administration's Control Tower of negligence of duty . Therefore , the result of the investigation by Taoyuan prosecutor's office will draw all the more attention .
If Arafat Abides by US Cease-fire Agreement , Cheney will Hold Bilateral Talks
