Another Warning for Global Warming , Antarctic Ice Shelf Collapsed
( Auckland , Syndicated news ) The experts at the US National Snow and Ice Data Center said yesterday that an Antarctic ice shelf has completely collapsed and broken up into thousands of icebergs . This is the largest single event of its kind over the last 30 years and therefore sends another warning about the global warming .
It is reported that the Larsen B Ice Shelf of 3,250 square kilometers on the eastern side of the Antarctic Peninsula has completely disintegrated in a 35 - day period .
The Center warned that with the advent of the hot summer season , the other ice shelves are also on the verge of disintegration .
This portends an increase in the rate of flow of glaciers in Antarctica , a rise in the global sea level and a threat to the lowland regions .
The Center at the University of Colorado says at its web site ( nsida . org ) that the Larsen B Ice Shelf that may have existed for 12,000 years and weighs 720 billion tons started to break up since January 31 of this year , and the ice fragments have formed thousands of drifting icebergs in the Weddell Sea .
The Center also indicated that the cause that led to the break-up of the ice shelf is the climate warming in the region .
More than Half of Britons Disapprove Government's Support of US Assault on Iraq
